#Approach:

Hinglish Approach:

Is question me DLL me jitne bhi nodes ka value target ke equal hai,
un sabko delete karna hai.

Step 1:
Temp pointer se poori DLL traverse karo.

Step 2:
Agar temp.val == target ho:
- prev node ko next node se connect karo
- next node ko prev node se connect karo

Step 3:
Agar delete hone wala node head hai,
to head ko head.next pe move karo

Step 4:
Traversal continue karo until temp becomes null

Important:
DLL me deletion ke time dono links handle karne hote hain:
prev.next
and
next.prev

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

/*Definition of doubly linked list:
class ListNode {
    int val;
    ListNode next;
    ListNode prev;

    ListNode() {
        val = 0;
        next = null;
        prev = null;
    }

    ListNode(int data1) {
        val = data1;
        next = null;
        prev = null;
    }

    ListNode(int data1, ListNode next1, ListNode prev1) {
        val = data1;
        next = next1;
        prev = prev1;
    }
}
 */

class Solution {
    public ListNode deleteAllOccurrences(ListNode head, int target) {

        ListNode temp = head;

        while(temp != null){
            if(temp.val == target){
                if(temp == head){
                    head = head.next;
                }
                ListNode prevNode = temp.prev;
                ListNode nextNode = temp.next;

                if(prevNode != null){
                    prevNode.next = nextNode;
                }
                if(nextNode != null){
                    nextNode.prev = prevNode;
                }
                temp = nextNode;
            }
            else{
                temp = temp.next;
            }
        }
        return head;

    }
}
